import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data['day_of_week'] = data['day'].dt.day_name()
    data['hour'] = data['time'].dt.hour
    data = data.groupby(['day']).mean().reset_index()
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='day', y='count', data=data)
    chart.axhline(y=data['count'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Average Count')
    chart.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average count of events per day?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day_of_week'] = pd.Categorical(data['day_of_week'], categories=['Monday','Tuesday','Wednesday','Thursday','Friday','Saturday', 'Sunday'], ordered=True)
    data = data.sort_values('day_of_week')
    chart = sns.barplot(x='day_of_week', y='count', data=data, palette='Blues_d')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of events by day of the week?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
